                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <locus from="43r"/>
                            <title type="incomplete">Commentaries</title>
                            <textLang xml:lang="gez"/>
                            <note>The following commentaries are mentioned in the catalogue, but it is not clear whether this list is 
                            exhaustive, and whether they constitute one coherent or several separated works.
                            According to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/6PK4S4QF"><seg type="bookSection"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Hamrick2021Daniel"/><title level="a">Conflicting Traditions: The Interpretation of Daniel’s Four Kingdoms in the Ethiopic Commentary (Terg&lt;hi rend="sup"&gt;w&lt;/hi&gt;āmē) Tradition</title><title level="m">Four Kingdom Motifs before and beyond the Book of Daniel</title><title level="s">Themes in Biblical Narrative. Jewish and Christian Traditions</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">James R.</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hamrick</t:surname></author><editor><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Andrew B.</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Perrin</t:surname></editor><editor><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Loren T.</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Stuckenbruck</t:surname></editor><pubPlace>Leiden–Boston</pubPlace><publisher>Brill</publisher><date>2021</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Themes in Biblical Narrative. Jewish and Christian Traditions</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">28</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="page">275-299</biblScope><biblScope unit="volume">28</biblScope><note type="url">https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.1163/j.ctv1sr6k2b.16?seq=1</note><citedRange unit="page">279</citedRange></bibl>, this manuscript
                                contains three distinct fragments of different versions of a <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6676CommDaniel">Commentary on Daniel (General record)</ref>.</note>
                            
